rComments: Very hard class but great prof.
He never showed up to his office hours and generally seemed disinterested in the course/students.

He's an excellent lecturer who was always extremely pleasant and answered all Q's.  Sometimes went into advanced theory which wasn't really necessary but overall he made the class very interesting and worth taking.  Tests were VERY difficult but he curved the class so it worked out.  2 group projects as a heads up which take many, many hours to do

Assignments are time consuming, which they need you have background in Time Series and deep R skills before you even taking the course.  Exams based on math skills, so suggest you take mathematical statistics before taking the course. Plus,  I'd recommend prepare another reference book as source. The textbook does not do fine for beginner.
